        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Kingston Jamaica</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>14 Nover 1844</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Business has brought me to <add>?</add>, and I<lb/> am therefore
                enabled to reply to your favor of <date>9 Oct</date> last.<lb/> When I wrote to you
                about the spiced Beef, I thought there<lb/> was some establishment in your city or
                in <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> for the putting up Beef for Exportation—If
                however<lb/> appears from your letter there is no such estbl., I shall<lb/> not
                therefore trouble you, as I find I may be able to<lb/> procure the article as I
                cheap from <placeName>London</placeName>—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I notice with great attention your observation<lb/> on the state of
                Judaism in <placeName>America</placeName> &amp; your propose=<lb/>tion to establish
                a Tract society for the benefit &amp; in<lb/>formation of the <hi rend="underline"
                    >poor</hi>. But I am of opinion my<lb/> dear Friend, that we should labour to
                excite the<lb/> minds of the wealthy &amp; bring them to a proper<lb/> sense of
                correctness, when shall succeed in this,<lb/> then of necessity will the poor follow
                the example<lb/> of those to whom they are in a great measure<lb/> indebted for
                their common means of support.<lb/> This not to say the poor are ignorant, but I
                tell you<lb/> the Rich are criminally so, this by their example,<lb/> of outrage
                against religious ordinances, that the<lb/> poor follow, &amp; when they see one who
                walks in a<lb/> high sphere of life violating these principles, they<lb/> (the poor)
                    <add>?</add>
                <add>?</add> of this as an excuse to <add>?</add>
                <add>?</add><lb/> their guilt. I know it is so <hi rend="underline">here</hi>, &amp;
                if any<lb/> opinion is not wrong, then it is so in other places<lb/> I shall however
                think over this subject, &amp; introduce<lb/> it to the consideration of our people
                here.</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>I can hear nothing about the Book you state you have<lb/> sent me. I fear the vessel
                was bound to <placeName><sic>Montigo</sic> Bay</placeName><lb/> thence it has not
                reached me. Who did you direct<lb/> it to? Thus it is your Occidents are so long
                reaching<lb/> us—you should be more particular in your<lb/> information whenever you
                send us your works<lb/> or any other.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I send you a statement of our a/c from last<lb/> settlement.
                Namely</p>
            <p>
                <date>Mar 1843</date>
            </p>
            <table cols=" 2" rows="8 ">
                <row>
                    <cell>1 set Books sold for</cell>
                    <cell>4.16.0 stg<add>?</add></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>1 do extra bound...</cell>
                    <cell>5. 8.0</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>2 setts Blinds....</cell>
                    <cell>4. 4.0</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>1 set Books.....</cell>
                    <cell>5. - -</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>1 set Do <persName>Lopez</persName> ...</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rend="underline">4.16.0</hi>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell>24:4:0</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>cash remitted acts 4 3 .....</cell>
                    <cell>
                        <hi rend="underline">15</hi>
                    </cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell><add>?</add> 9:4.0</cell>
                </row>
            </table>
            <p>This is the Bals<add>?</add> I requested</p>
            <p><persName>Mr Peixotto</persName> to pay you for me. <persName>Mr Joseph</persName>
                has<lb/> to settle for 1 set <hi rend="underline">you</hi> sent <hi rend="underline"
                    >him</hi>. &amp; our set he<lb/> owes me for—Both of which he will arrange
                for<lb/> by flyer. deducting duties paid &amp; 11$ advanced<lb/> poor <add>?</add>
                <del>for</del> on same a/c. also some of your<lb/> catechisms <hi rend="underline"
                    >he</hi> sold. I have on hand for you<lb/> some of the Daily prayer Books, I
                believe 2 <hi rend="underline">sets</hi><lb/> &amp; some of your other Books. I gave
                over to <persName>DCordova</persName><lb/> your Sermons, but I believe he has such
                done<lb/> much with them. You can look into this<lb/> statement &amp; if there is
                any thing you wish<lb/> to be explained I will gladly do so. Do not sup=<lb/>pose I
                would sacrifice your Books, I say so,<lb/> because you write, “I hope the 41$ and
                are <hi rend="underline">not</hi><lb/> “all you have got for the 2 sets of prayer
                Books<lb/> “as that would be less than I sell them for here &amp;c<lb/> “&amp;c”</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>but I think you are thinking of the 2 sets I<lb/> offered to <persName>Rev
                    Lindo</persName>—but which he did not take<lb/> if so you are in error, &amp;
                you are richer in<lb/> Books here, than you expected.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The “First Fruits” seem bl<add>?</add>—you know<lb/> you already
                think I am <hi rend="underline">prejudiced</hi>, therefore<lb/> I will be silent
                when <persName>Nathan</persName> is in question</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">God bless you, &amp; keep you in his<lb/> keeping are the prayer
                of</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Yours Sincerely</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">M<add>?</add> M Sollas</persName>
            </p>
            <p><persName>Mr Alexr. Moralles</persName> mentioned to me<lb/> that he offered 2 ½ $
                when called to<lb/> Sepher in <placeName>Phda</placeName>, which he left with<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. T. Tucker</persName> of <persName>Jas Barclay's</persName>,
                    <placeName>South<lb/> Wharfs</placeName>, to hand over to you—if not<lb/> get
                paid, please apply for it &amp;<lb/> let me know if its paid<add>?</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <hi rend="underline">
                    <persName role="author">MS</persName>
                </hi>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <persName role="author">M M. Sollis</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Kingston Ja</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>Nov 14?/44</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">The <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">via—</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>
            </p>
